reviews:
Purchased for my wife to use in Fall/Spring type weather in Canada. She said they fit great, keep her hands warm, and the touchscreen part works well - also works great for unlocking the touch sensor on the Toyota Camry door. They might be ok as a driving glove even in winter, Will update if there are any issues in the coldest parts of winter (Jan/Feb)
Currently has worked well down to -8C or so that it has gotten to in the past week since these arrived.

reviews: Every winter I lose my gloves so after misplacing my leather ones I got these ones since they look good and are touchscreen friendly.
